          <div property="content:encoded" class="field-item even"><p>This how-to guide describes how to set up automatic machine-based translations for content on a Drupal site. Whenever a node is created, translation jobs will be created for every language specified, and depending on how you set up your translator, you should be able to completely automate the translation process. For this project we are using SDL, but you should be able to use other translators. </p>
<p><strong>1. Download and enable the translation management modules</strong>. This can be done through Drush or through the modules interface in drupal.</p>
